title: For Sale/Trade:  Norinco NHM91 (RPK) for sale!
postcontent: Howdy- I am selling/trading my Norinco NHM91! If you don't know much about these guns, they are some of the better AKs ever imported into America. Thicker receiver and barrel means more accuracy and better sustained fire, along with generally being more robust and harder to break. The gun has had about 1000 rounds down the barrel; nothing corrosive and a vast majority of it being Golden Tiger. All parts on the gun are original and all serial numbers are matching. Bolt, Bolt carrier, and piston are all in the white, as factory. This gun was imported with a 20 inch RPK profile barrel, Chrome lined and cold hammer forged. I'm not sure 7.62 x 39 benefits tons from the extra barrel length, however if you were looking to build this into an RPK or other DMR roll AK, the longer barrel will be critical- if not, there is some velocity gained by the extra 4 inches. Or cut it down and make it 16, who the hell cares. It's your gun!Right now the gun is sporting a set of Bulgarian furniture, minus the handguard which is a Romanian dong. I planned on keeping the dong and selling with a regular Bulgy hand guard... unless otherwise per$uaded. Original furniture and sling will be included, as will a 30 round surplus Euro magazine. These guns are phenomenal collector pieces; assuming you were the kind Collector who also enjoys shooting their hardware ;D i'm looking to either get cash plus a trade or a straight across trade (any gun valued ~950.) I can make up the difference should you want to trade something worth more as well. I'm open to literally ANY fire arms trades, rifle, pistol, multi gun, etc. I'm not an asshole so don't be one either! Thank you!!

title: For Sale:  Sig P320C 9mm 3.9" 15rds with Apex+
postcontent: For Sale - Very very good condition Sig P320C 9mm 3.9" with Apex trigger DA/SA Black with Contrast Sights and "M" Lower. Comes with 6, 15rd Sig OEM magazines, original case (matching serial), Apex light weight flat trigger, original trigger with Sig OEM replaccment spring, gun lacok, and Sig OEM OWB holster. I would say like new, but when you look on the inside upper part of the slide, you will notice where the factory black has worn. While this is completely normal and expected, I do believe it makes it less than "like new". The rails and barrel are still shiny black and show no signs of wear at all - I'm a fan of grease even on poly pistols. According to the case, it was made on Oct 18, 2016 and of course, made in the USA. The P320C is the Compact - not the Carry. The Carry and the Compact vary by the number of rounds for the OEM magazines - 17 vs 15 and the Compact, the weight - the Compact is slightly lighter weight than the Carry when empty, and the height - the Compact is shorter than the Carry.This is a Gen 2 P320C 9mm. The main noticible difference is the slide catch is completely enclosed versus the Gen 1 where there was only a small 'slash' below the slide catch - a huge improvement over the Gen 1 IMO. I call them Gen 1 and Gen 2, not Sig. Sig Sauer makes no mention of the lower differences at all, so be aware if you're buying an X-Change Kit or want a different size lower. The FCU is not any different from what I can tell. Use = about 750 rounds of Speer Lawman and Gold Dot 124 are the only rounds ever used on this pistol. The 124 seems to be the sweet spot for the 9mm P320 and I’ve owned/own the Full-size, Carry, Compact, and Sub Compact. The pistol will sell with 6 - 15rd Sig magazines. Yes 6 and not knock-offs, but Sig brand magazines. If you see the orange dot on the front blade, that is NOT an updated sight. I used epoxy day glow orange paint on the standard factory sights. It make target acquisition much faster but it’s only paint and not an upgraded sight. This is a very well taken care of firearm, which you will realize as soon as you see it. Also comes with an updated flat Apex trigger and spring. I also have the original trigger as well as another new in bag Sig factory trigger spring, in case you want to send it back for repair etc. it’s a Sig so Lifetine Warranty! Includes the P320C 9mm 2nd Gen pistol, original case, owners manual, OEM trigger with new OEM trigger srping, 6 15rd Sig magazines, and gun lock. Price is rock solid $475. I don’t like negotiating price and this is by far a very fair price for this setup. No trades, no shipping, cash only, in person only.So so why am I selling? I bought a P226 Legion. I still have my P320CA (Carry) 9mm Carry that I use for EDC - it also has the Apex flar trigger. I live on James Island and prefer you come to my house for sale. I can also meet at my work in Mount Pleasant. You will need to bring your current CWP or a valid SC Drivers License.
